#Text=Commentators likened the legal conflict between Beck and the site to the Streisand effect , a phenomenon where an individual 's attempt to censor material on the Internet in turn proves to make the material itself more public .

#Text=Online Media Daily commented , " The decision appears to mark a significant win for digital rights advocates because a ruling in Beck 's favor could have encouraged other subjects of online parodies to take their complaints directly to the WIPO rather than U.S. courts , which are bound by the First Amendment . "

column1: #Text=Eiland-Hall 's website was still operational Monday , at a mirror site www.GB1990.com.
#Text=At the site , Eiland-Hall announced " WE WON ! " .
#Text=He gave Beck well-wishes as the commentator is recovering from appendicitis .
#Text=Interview
#Text=Can you describe a little bit about yourself and your background , and how you came to be interested in the Glenn Beck meme in the first place ?
#Text=I 've been a computer geek since 1987 , when I was 12 .
#Text=I 've been on the internet since 1994 .
#Text=Among other jobs , I 've done technical support and web design/hosting .
#Text=I 've gone back to school and I 'm working on a degree in Computer Science .
#Text=If I manage that , I 'm thinking of following up with a Master 's in Meteorology .
#Text=If I had more courage , I 'd probably try to become a professional storm chaser .
#Text=I grew up as a very fundamentalist Southern Baptist .
#Text=I got better .
#Text=My political and social outlook has gone from very conservative to very liberal .
#Text=One nice thing about this is that I understand both sides .
#Text=A lot of liberals scoff at the concept of Chick tracts , for example ; and I do , now .
#Text=But growing up , I remember believing in all that stuff .

#Text=I do have to remind myself that most Christians are pretty moderate in their outlook , though , sometimes when I get a little frustrated by some of the more vocal small groups who would like the U.S. to become a Christian Theocracy .

#Text=I 've also become frustrated with radicals -- liberal and conservative ; though , as a liberal , you 'll be shocked - shocked , I say - to find out that I see more conservatives that fit the bill -- radicals who I feel are tearing this country apart with their manipulations and lies .
#Text=These extremists are pushing people toward the extremes , and it 's polarizing and ripping our nation apart .
#Text=It seems like nobody wants to compromise any longer ; nobody wants to try and work together ; everybody wants their party to win at all costs , because the other party is the spawn of Satan .
